Portable Windows 11 USB Flash Drive with Rufus and Windows To Go
What is Windows To Go?
Windows To Go is a feature in Windows 10 Enterprise and Windows 10 Education that enables the creation of a Windows To Go workspace that can be booted from a USB-connected external drive on PCs. -https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/deployment/planning/windows-to-go-overview
Prerequisites
A USB flash drive, at least 32 GB https://amzn.to/3qkrJ1p | https://amzn.to/3Nhu9b9
Windows 11 installation media .iso
Installing Windows 11 on USB
Plug in the USB flash drive, 32GB or larger
Download the Windows 11 iso Download
Download Rufus version 2.0 or later Download
Run the Rufux application
Select the target USB device (double check the selection, all data on the USB device will be destroyed)
Click the Select button next to Disk or ISO image > Browse to and select the downloaded Windows 11 iso file
Select Windows To Go from the Image option dropdown
Select MBR from the Partition scheme dropdown
Click the Start button to write the modified installation media to the target USB device
Wait for Rufus to write the files to the USB device
That's it! Boot to the USB device on any machine you wish to run the portable Windows 11 environment on
 
